  <description><![CDATA[<p><a name="Top"></a></p>
<p> </p>
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><a data-udi="umb://document/c54eeaf670ee47ba97f163f4a1f83fa5" href="/{localLink:umb://document/c54eeaf670ee47ba97f163f4a1f83fa5}#Highlights" title="Milan &amp; Lake Como" data-anchor="#Highlights">Highlights</a> | <a data-udi="umb://document/c54eeaf670ee47ba97f163f4a1f83fa5" href="/{localLink:umb://document/c54eeaf670ee47ba97f163f4a1f83fa5}#Itinerary" title="Milan &amp; Lake Como" data-anchor="#Itinerary">Itinerary</a> | <a data-udi="umb://document/c54eeaf670ee47ba97f163f4a1f83fa5" href="/{localLink:umb://document/c54eeaf670ee47ba97f163f4a1f83fa5}#Includes" title="Milan &amp; Lake Como" data-anchor="#Includes">Your holiday includes</a> | <a data-udi="umb://document/c54eeaf670ee47ba97f163f4a1f83fa5" href="/{localLink:umb://document/c54eeaf670ee47ba97f163f4a1f83fa5}#Hotels" title="Milan &amp; Lake Como" data-anchor="#Hotels">Hotels</a> | <a data-udi="umb://document/c54eeaf670ee47ba97f163f4a1f83fa5" href="/{localLink:umb://document/c54eeaf670ee47ba97f163f4a1f83fa5}#Dates" title="Milan &amp; Lake Como" data-anchor="#Dates">Departure dates</a></h2>
<p> </p>
<h3 style="color: #00533a;"><a name="Tour highlights"></a>Highlights</h3>
<ul>
<li>Hit up two of <a data-udi="umb://document/a1a80922d88a43f8ba80b182c72e8904" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a1a80922d88a43f8ba80b182c72e8904}" title="Italy">Italy's</a> most glam resorts on this multi-centre itinerary</li>
<li>Start in Milan and shop the designer boutiques, see the opera and admire the architecture</li>
<li>Spend a week in Lake Como taking boat trips along the lake and visiting the grand villas that line the shores</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<h3 style="color: #00533a;"><a name="Itinerary"></a>Itinerary</h3>
<p><strong>Day 1: UK to Milan</strong></p>
<p>Arrive in <a data-udi="umb://document/2575554a5b50446eb00d5bf533f317cd" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2575554a5b50446eb00d5bf533f317cd}" title="Milan">Milan</a> and take a transfer to your centrally-located hotel. Check in, unpack your bags and head straight into the city for a look around.</p>
<p><strong>Days 2-3: Milan</strong></p>
<p>There's so much to see and do in Milan. Visiting the Duomo is a must - stay outside and admire the architecture from the piazza or head inside. You can even climb to the roof for some pretty impressive views across the city. The Galleria Vittoria Emanuale is just next door. This is the world's oldest shopping mall and well worth a visit.</p>
<p>The museums here are ever changing and the galleries house some of the world's most famous pieces - The Last Supper calls Milan its home. Opera's pretty big here too with the Scala Theatre putting on impressive shows throughout the year. Our favourite Milan pastime is aperitivo - it was invented here so you can't leave without experiencing it.</p>
<p><strong>Day 4: Milan to Lake Como</strong></p>
<p>Today you'll be heading north to <a data-udi="umb://document/7d421e04a79044babf8cafda30e31d4a" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7d421e04a79044babf8cafda30e31d4a}" title="Lake Como">Lake Como</a>, Italy's most glamorous lake. The journey will take around an hour and a half.</p>
<p><strong>Days 5-10: Lake Como</strong></p>
<p>Lake Como looks almost like a painting. The waters are ink blue and back-dropped by a dramatic mountain scene. Our favourite way to explore is by boat. Jump on a ferry and make your way between resorts or release your inner James Bond and opt for a speedboat trip up the lake. You'll spot lots of grand villas on the shore - visit Villa Balbienello to see the manicured gardens and framed lake views. </p>
<p>The towns are great to stop off in for lunch. Our favourite is <a data-udi="umb://document/d3611d3782e0494ead59e534458bcdd6" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d3611d3782e0494ead59e534458bcdd6}" title="Bellagio">Bellagio</a> where there's lots of restaurants and shops to visit. Quieter resorts like <a data-udi="umb://document/164b7f39f6d74033a2991f5799ebdfa7" href="/{localLink:umb://document/164b7f39f6d74033a2991f5799ebdfa7}" title="Lenno">Lenno</a> have their own charm too and are a great option for escaping the crowds. </p>
<p><strong>Day 11: Lake Como to UK</strong></p>
<p>Wave goodbye to the lake, maybe squeezing in one last coffee by the water, before taking a transfer to Milan airport for your journey home.</p>
<p> </p>
<h3 style="color: #00533a;"><a name="Includes"></a>Your holiday includes</h3>
<ul>
<li>Return flights from the UK</li>
<li>Transfers from Milan airport to your hotel, Milan to Lake Como and from Lake Como to the airport</li>
<li>10 nights accommodation</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p style="color: #00533a;"><strong>Your holiday excludes:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Excursions</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<h3 style="color: #00533a;"><a name="Hotels"></a>Hotels</h3>
<p>Choose from any of our hotels in <a data-udi="umb://document/2575554a5b50446eb00d5bf533f317cd" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2575554a5b50446eb00d5bf533f317cd}" title="Milan">Milan</a> or <a data-udi="umb://document/7d421e04a79044babf8cafda30e31d4a" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7d421e04a79044babf8cafda30e31d4a}" title="Lake Como">Lake Como</a>. You can change the durations to create your perfect holiday. Give us a call to discuss your options.</p>
<p> </p>
<h3 style="color: #00533a;"><a name="Dates"></a>Departure dates</h3>
<p>Flexible daily departures from May to October.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a data-udi="umb://document/c54eeaf670ee47ba97f163f4a1f83fa5" href="/{localLink:umb://document/c54eeaf670ee47ba97f163f4a1f83fa5}#Top" title="Milan &amp; Lake Como" data-anchor="#Top">[Back to top]</a></p>]]></description>
